Text: This week we finished off the proposal and presentation relatively smoothly.
Communication wasÂ  better than last week and everyone showed to any meetings we had planned.
Everyone is also getting used to each other and there is a better sense of having a team spirit.
There hasn't really been any conflict in our team yet and our group seems to be open to ideas that might be better than their own if suggestions pop up.
The technical approach to the project has gone about smoothly and everyone seems pretty relaxed about the whole project.
Things to improve on as a team.
We needed to have more time between getting out slides and proposals done, to proof read and double check our content.
Although there was a relatively short amount of time to get things done, being more organised would have improved the quality of our presentation.
I also noticed that during the Q and A session of the presentation, we offered different answers to what we had in our proposal.

To address these issues next time, I will try to make sure we get started on our final presentation earlier and double check with everyone if they had everything they wanted on the slides and also check through the slides myself to see if we had any gaps in our content.
Our communication has greatly improved this week, with people showing up to scheduled meetings and responding to messages.
We have changed our main messaging app from discord to Facebook messenger to make it more convenient for everyone.
Things I could do better.
At the moment I feel that my main challenge is to make sure I ask enough questions and do enough research to understand each aspect of the project we are working on.
For example, I am still unsure exactly how a LAMP stack works.
This is important for me as I would like to be able pick up all the concepts in our project so I would be able to implement them myself later if needed.
To help deal with these knowledge gaps I will try to do small sub tasks for each step, ask questions and use online resources to get to make sure I've got a full understanding of everything.
Goals for next week.
On Friday, we decided to assign a "product" to each team member so we are leading a specific aspect of the project.
I was assigned to manage the parsing side of the project, so I will need to organise the overall approach to getting the data, transforming it and getting it into the database.
This means that for next week I will try to design an overall approach to the task and create sub-tasks that could be tackled by teammates.
As a team we will post these sub tasks onto trello to keep track of who is doing what.
General thoughts.

I'm feeling a lot more relaxed so far in this project than the last one, I feel more confident in learning new concepts and my team overall does not seem overly stressed with many aspects of the project.
However, I am aware that this demeanour may also be because of overconfidence, so I will still work hard on this project to learn as much I can and make sure we deliver a great product.
